    <note>Kang(1) Yuzhi [896] His grandfather, Shi [3434], who held a minor office, moved from Henan, Luoyang to Huaining, Yuanqiu xian. His father, Zhuo [3432], fled his post as prefect of Linjiang when it was attacked by rebels. Yuzhi, who moved to Jiaxing at the beginning of the Southern Song, presented policy proposals in 1127. When Qin(1) Gui [8008] became chief minister, he became a patron of Yuzhi's career, which ended when Qin Gui died. XNYL, 156.18a, 157.10b; SHY:ZG, 70.32b; Songshi yi, 27.19a. CBD, 3, 2103.</note>
